    <item>
      <title>Safe git force push</title>
      <link>https://fetinin.github.io/blog/posts/safe-git-force-push/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 16 Nov 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://fetinin.github.io/blog/posts/safe-git-force-push/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You&amp;rsquo;ve likely been in this situation before. You make some minor code fixes, do &lt;code&gt;git commit --amend&lt;/code&gt; to add them to the current commit, and do &lt;code&gt;git push --force&lt;/code&gt;. Then, you happily open pull request and see that you&amp;rsquo;ve deleted you&amp;rsquo;re colleagues commit.😩&lt;/p&gt;</description>
